    <main>
        <h1>Echoes of Time</h1>

        <section>
            <h2>Description</h2>
            <div class="about-text">
                <p>
                    Developed at CalHacks 12.0 at UC Berkeley, Echoes of Time is a sophisticated multimodal web application that synchronizes 
                    visual narrative with original auditory composition. The platform utilizes a custom-built Node.js backend to orchestrate a complex 
                    AI pipeline, beginning with the automated extraction of video frames at one-second intervals from user-uploaded MP4 files. 
                    These frames are processed by Google Gemini 1.5 Flash to conduct a comprehensive vision analysis, identifying thematic elements, 
                    emotional cues, and environmental ambiance. This metadata is then translated into precise descriptive prompts for the Lyria-002 
                    music generation model, which synthesizes a bespoke 30-second soundtrack tailored to the specific mood and pacing of the visual content.
                </p>
                <p>&nbsp;</p>
                <p>
                    The application prioritizes a professional user experience through a minimalist, responsive interface featuring drag-and-drop 
                    functionality and real-time processing updates. Beyond simple media conversion, Echoes of Time provides an explainable AI component by presenting
                    users with a detailed reasoning summary that justifies the musical choices—such as instrumentation and tempo—based on the detected visual elements. 
                    Engineered for scalability within the Google Cloud ecosystem, the project demonstrates a seamless integration of Vertex AI, high-performance API management, 
                    and modern frontend design to push the boundaries of creative expression through generative technology.
                </p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section>
            <h2>Technologies</h2>
            <p class="about-text">Google Gemini 1.5 Flash, Google Lyria-002, Vertex AI API, Node.js, Express.js, JavaScript (ES6+), HTML5, CSS3, Google Cloud Platform, Multimodal AI, Video-to-Text Analysis, Music Synthesis, Frame Extraction, RESTful Architecture, Drag-and-Drop API</p>
        </section>

